data.name: pbx264PresetWarning.ToolTip
data.value: For real time encoding like screen recording it is recommended to select fast as possible preset. Otherwise it can't keep up with recording and a lot of frame drops will happen.

data.name: cbx264Preset.ToolTip
data.value: Faster preset = Faster encoding but higher file size. Slower preset = Slower encoding but lower file size. For real time encoding (e.g. screen recording), the preset must be as fast as possible.

data.name: nudx264CRF.ToolTip
data.value: Constant Rate Factor (CRF): The value can be between 0-51, where 0 is lossless, 30 is default, and 51 is the worst possible. A higher value means bad quality, but a low file size.

data.name: nudXvidQscale.ToolTip
data.value: 1 being highest quality/largest filesize and 31 being the lowest quality/smallest filesize.

data.name: nudGIFBayerScale.ToolTip
data.value: Controls the Bayer Scale index, a higher scale will display more banding. Default is 2.
